<TITLE> ACC sues Hasina for Tk 3 crore graft </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Anti-corruption Commission Sunday filed a case against Sheikh Hasina and six others on charges of corruption worth Tk 3 crore with Tejgaon Police Station. The case, filed at about 4:00pm with Tejgaon Police Station, alleges irregularities in a Khulna power plant and purchase of land for Bangabandhu Memorial Trust, Tejgaon police chief Jane Alam said. ACC assistant director SM Sabbir Hossain filed the case. According to case details, Hasina received Tk 3 crore in eight cheques and pay orders of American Express Bank, Standard Chartered Bank, Eastern Bank, Dhaka Bank, Arab Bangladesh Bank and formerly ANZ Grindlays in different times from October 20, 1996 to November 24, 1997. Local representatives of Wartsila Power Development Ltd Consortium paid the money. The FIR of the case said that the then prime minister Hasina received the bribe at the Prime Minister's Office. She bought a two-storey building on 19 katha 11 chhatak land at Dhanmondi road no. 32 (Old), holding no. 678 for Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Memorial Trust for Tk 6.50 crore, it alleged. Former power secretary Dr Toufiq-e-Elahi Chowdhury and former chairman of Power Development Board Nooruddin Mahmud Kamal have also been accused of having had their roles in the corruption. The latest case brings the number of corruption-extortion cases against the Awami League chief to fourall filed during the state of emergency. Two cases were filed against Hasina with Tejgaon and Gulshan police stations on June 13 on extortion charges. The two cases charged her with taking Tk 8.99 crore in exchange for giving permission for setting up power plants. Businessman Noor Ali filed the case with Tejgaon Police Station, also accusing Hasina's cousin Sheikh Helaluddin and his wife Rupa Chowdhury. Managing Director of business firm Eastcoast Trading Ltd Azam Jahangir Chowdhury filed the other case with Gulshan Police Station. Hasina's cousin and former health minister Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim has been made the main accused in the case. Another businessman Tajul Islam Faruk filed a Tk 3 crore extortion case against Hasina with Tejgaon Police Station on April 9. bdnews24.com
